# n8n Workflow Standards

Follow `.ai/rules/workflow-standards.md` and ADR-002 (`docs/13-decisions/002-n8n-orchestration-only.md`).

## n8n MAY

- Call external HTTP APIs (Outlook, SharePoint, SES, court systems)
- Transform payload format for external systems
- Retry HTTP calls with configured backoff
- Route on simple flags sent by FastAPI (e.g., `skipEmail: true`)
- Callback to FastAPI internal webhook with HMAC signature

## n8n MUST NOT

- Contain business rules or legal logic
- Make authorization decisions
- Store authoritative case/client data
- Write to PostgreSQL (no PostgreSQL nodes)
- Be exposed to public internet
- Directly notify end users without FastAPI audit trail

## Workflow Naming

`n8n/workflows/{domain}/{action}-v{N}.json` — e.g., `intake-new-client-v1.json`

## Webhook Contract

- FastAPI → n8n: `X-LexFlow-Signature`, `X-Correlation-Id`, `X-Execution-Id`
- n8n → FastAPI: `X-N8N-Signature`, callback to `/api/v1/internal/webhooks/n8n/{slug}`
- Reference: `docs/06-workflows/webhook-contracts.md`, `.ai/patterns/n8n-workflow-pattern.md`

## Promotion

Dev → staging (PR merge) → production (manual approval). Never activate smoke/test workflows for live traffic.

Reference: `docs/06-workflows/promotion-pipeline.md`, `.ai/tasks/create-workflow.md`
